"If you want to get a real experience on culture and values of South Asia, particularly from Bangladesh, without leaning Toronto, you should come to Taylor Massey neighbourhood.This is because most of the residents in this neighbourhood are form the above mentioned part of the world" - Anonymous
 "This is a very multicultural neighbourhood, people are welcoming and supportive to new immigrants" - Rezanul Karim

Linda - Linda is one of the founding members of TPANA (Teesdale Pro-Active Neighbourhood Association). She volunteers with numerous organizations including the food bank in Taylor Massey and Neighbourhood Link. She is an advocate of community safety and helps out the elderly in her community.
Rezwanul Karim (Adult 25-59) - Rezwan is a community leader in Taylor Massey who dedicates his time and efforts to the ANC office as a part-time facilitator. He has extensive knowledge in agricultural practices (food security and community garden start-ups). Rezwan, who speaks Bengali, Urdu, and Hindi, is also associated with the Local Immigration Partnership Project (LIPP).
Ann (Adult 25-59) - Ann is one of the founding members of TPANA, tenant representative of 30 Teesdale, and former chair of the Teesdale Service Network. She advocates neighbourhood cooperation and neighbourhood safety. Ann helps out her community by facilitating communication and by volunteering at the Daily Food Bank.
